Text.SourceString: A farmer? Okay.//I’m <NPCName>Kira</>.
See you around, kid.
Anybody can play the flute. All you need to do is get yourself one and blow through the mouthpiece.
It’s easy to learn but really hard to master.
I made my first flute myself. It was just a way to relax after a long day of combat.
I used to bring food and camp in the cave for days… Not anymore.
I guess my wild days are over.
It’s Tuesday?! No! Is it?
It’s hard to keep track of the days, living so deep in the forest.
Check out my board. I’ll give you rewards when you slay certain monsters.
It makes my job easier.//Not so hard to understand, is it?
Cooking isn’t for me. I’m more the flower-arranging type.
Sure, you can do both. I’m just not a good cook.
I used to bring food and camp in the cave for days… Not anymore.
I guess my wild days are over.
Why do you keep saying it’s Tuesday? It isn’t… It’s Thursday.
Oh! It isn’t. Today’s Friday. It’s hard to keep track of the days, living so deep in the forest.

Are you going to the cave or coming back?
Today? No, I don’t want to hunt today. Thanks… Actually, I like to hunt alone…
<NPCName>Dinda</> got me this flute on New Year’s ages ago.//<portrait=normal>I don’t celebrate birthdays, but it was the most thoughtful gift I’ve ever gotten.
It plays much better than my old one.
I can’t wait for yoga on Saturdays. It’s a great reason to go to town.
Lies. I do not like yoga Saturdays.//<portrait=normal>But <NPCName>Jack</> likes to go down to Starlet Town, so it’s worth the trouble… At least I get to see him happy.

We need to take care of them because they take care of us in combat.
Playing the flute makes your core strong because your lungs get a workout.
You didn’t know that?… Hmm. Well, now you do.
I still visit the cavern, but not a lot.
I just got up. I could use a good stretch right now.
Have you fought all the monsters on my board?
Then why are you here, kid?
Check on my board often.//I might have old things I need to get rid of.
I can tell you some legends. What kind do you want to hear?

Well, that’s true, not a legend. Monsters and ghouls once took over the forest.//<portrait=normal>Nobody was guarding the cave, so they were everywhere. For a while, you couldn’t even go in the forest.
I’m sick of tortillas. That’s all I used to eat.//<portrait=annoyed>Tortillas this, tortillas that.
Can’t stand them anymore. I hate them now.

The mayor told us all about Pufferfish yesterday.
I don’t get involved in corporate drama. I’m focus my energy on the actual monsters that live in the cavern.
Come talk to me if you have questions about combat.
Fishing? I don’t know much about fishing.
If you feel like you’re going to pass out, stop and eat something.//It’ll make you feel better.
You don’t want to pass out, because who knows what creatures are in the cavern.//<portrait=normal>They could steal your stuff.
The soil is softer now the ice has melted. I can only imagine how many weeds there must be on your farm.
I’m sure you have plenty of work to do to get the farm going again.
You need to train more if you want to get better at combat.
Just like fishing… There’s no way around it.
There’s different kinds of armor and weapons you can get, either by finding or buying them from merchants.
Each will give you a different kind of protection and strength.//<portrait=annoyed>For combat. What did you think I was talking about?

Listen to my advice or not. Do what you want.
Some people fish. I slay monsters. We all have our vices.
Not vices, I guess. Things. We all have our things… Hobbies. Whatever.
What monsters you encounter depends on how deep in the cavern you go.
The season has nothing to do with where the monsters are. They’re all there, just on different levels.//Why are you asking so many questions? You should just go and hunt already.
I had way too much pumpkin pie for dinner last night.
I think I ate enough pumpkin pie for a year.//<portrait=normal>But I wouldn’t say no to more if there’s leftovers.

Thanks. Now you should tell the other islanders that.//They seem to think I like visitors, for some reason.

Figure out your strength. And bring some armor!
I think we all can use rainy days like this.
No need to water my garden today.
I’m sure I’m not the only one who likes the smell of rain.
Mmm… You smell that?
Why are there so many things in this house? I never really noticed before.
I’m sure I’m not the only one who likes the smell of rain.
Mmm… You smell that?
I think we all can use rainy days like this.
No need to water my garden today.
It’s too bright in here. The sun’s hurting my eyes… And it’s loud in here.
I have to get back to the cabin.
No combat this weekend?
Vacationing?
I’m here to learn how to stretch correctly.<NPCName>Leah</>’s learning from videos on the internet.//<portrait=happy>You heard about those?
I’m going to buy the videos and do them at home. That way, I don’t need to come here.
It’s hard to succeed at combat if you’re not coordinated.
You have it, <PlayerName>$player</>! And I don’t say that lightly. Keep it up!
I have to dig out some of my old blades one of these days.
Clean off the rust… Sell them. I don’t know.
It’s impossible to live alone without people bothering you, isn’t it?
Fodder? Food for animals? No, I don’t have any. You’ve come to the wrong place.

Up there, see the barns? You can buy it there… You passed the building, kid.//<portrait=happy>Also, I’d go and see <NPCName>Charlie</> if I were you. Might need to get a checkup for that disorientation.
<NPCName>Charles</>? Yes, that’s what I said.
You can try using your farming tool to fight monsters, but I don’t know how far it’ll get ya.
Check out my list over there. I’ll give you rewards when you slay certain monsters.
Bring me the monsters first. Okay?
The barn’s kind of a mess… It hasn’t been lived in for years. <NPCName>Jack</> used to live there before we got married… Rotten now.
It’s been empty ever since… Cobwebs. Rats. Gah.
I’m here for a routine checkup. How else am I going to keep healthy?
These folks seem to know what they’re talking about.//Especially <NPCName>Charlie</>… I like him. He’s the straightforward type.
Huh? Who’s <NPCName>Charles</>?
I don’t want to scare you, but you should keep those vitamins handy when you go into combat.
They help me recover instantly… Ask the doctors if you don’t believe me.
Well, yeah, they don’t taste good, but we don’t get them for the taste.//We take medicine to get better, fast.
You sound like my son, <NPCName>Kenny</>.
When he was seven.
<NPCName>Jack</> needs extra help stocking the shelves. Not a hard job, just time-consuming, that’s all.
If you need anything, you should talk to <NPCName>Jack</>. I don’t know much about selling these.
How’s the old cabin? Holding up okay?
The house?//<portrait=normal>Oh, the cabin, you mean? There are some people from the Band of Smile inside the guild.
I don't really care about birthdays or parties in general.
Yeah, they're alright. Some people make such a big deal out of it.
Gah. You're one of those <Italic>chippery</> ones.

Special.SourceString: I don't mind. Birthdays are kind of fun.

Text.SourceString: It can be any date I want it to be.//What's with the personal question?
It isn't listed. I don't celebrate it.//Personal reason.

Special.SourceString: I don't remember ever seeing your birthday on calendar.
